snippet: Taiwan also said it had stopped accepting applications for Filipino workers, retaliating for the killing of a fisherman by the Philippine Coast Guard.
abstract: Taiwan announces withdrawal of its representative in Manila and says it has stopped accepting applications for Filipino workers, retaliatory step for killing of Taiwanese fisherman by Philippine Coast Guard.

byline.contributor: Floyd Whaley contributed reporting from Manila.

lead_paragraph: Taiwan also said it had stopped accepting applications for Filipino workers, retaliating for the killing of a fisherman by the Philippine Coast Guard.

headline.seo: Taiwan Recalls Envoy in Manila Over Killing
headline.main: Taiwan Recalls Its Envoy in Manila Over a Killing
